summary: Captain Marvel: The History of Goose the Cat
title: Captain Marvel: The History of Goose the Cat
excerpt: Everything you need to know about Captain Marvel's feline — or is it flerken? — companion...
description: If you saw the Captain Marvel trailer or poster, you may have noticed Carol Danvers’ furry friend. That little fuzzball is known in the comics as Chewie, Carol’s temperamental cat. For Marvel’s March 8th Captain Marvel movie, Carol’s pet cat is named Goose. While it’s a bummer that we’re losing the Star Wars reference and original name, at least Goose is still a period-appropriate pop culture reference (Top Gun), for which Carol is known, and still a fellow pilot to boot… [Read More]

body:

At this point Captain Marvel‘s IMAX pre-sales are out-pacing previous superhero movies such as Wonder Woman, Deadpool 2 and Thor: Ragnarok. When Captain Marvelhits theaters worldwide next week, it’ll be on 1,360 IMAX…

summary: while i do not agree with your stand with captain marvel i can respect it and ask what female super heros you like?
question: while i do not agree with your stand with captain marvel i can respect it and ask what female super heros you like?
answer:
Ok first off, thank you so much anon, just because we don’t see eye to eye on everything, doesn’t mean we can’t respect the others opinion on something and act like a adult about it, so thank you for that.

I honestly feel like if Brie had just calmed down with her extreme feminist stand I could have liked this movie much more and at one time I was excited for it, but now, I just roll my eyes at it and say no thanks.   

But the female super hero’s I grew up were supergirl and wonder woman, there were so many others, but those two stood out for me above all others. There have been female super hero’s for a very long time and I watched them all growing up, Brie did not invent it.
